Why one should travel more? ✈️ 

You might feel like you’re stuck in a rut in your daily life. Or you’re yearning for something exciting and different. You’re craving new experiences and new challenges. Travel is the ideal place to test yourself. It pushes people to their limits and gets them outside their comfort zone. You’ll discover how resourceful you are when you’re exposed to new places, people and experiences. Maybe it’s finding your way around a busy city. Or ordering a meal when you don’t speak the language. Or zip-lining. You’ll feel pride when you finish your trip successfully. Overcoming challenges will bring you joy and energy for future tests. You’ll realize how capable you are and build your confidence.❤️ 

.
.

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Everyone keeps saying how important it is to travel. So what's all this fuss about? Why do people travel and love travelling? 😕

More importantly: why should we travel more? 👀

The benefits of traveling are not just a one-time thing: traveling changes you physically and psychologically. Having little time or money isn't a valid excuse. You can fly for cheap very easily. If you have a full-time job and a family, you can still travel on the weekends or holidays. ✈ 

2020 has been a tough year for travel - to say the least. But don't let that discourage you from making travel plans in 2021! 😍✌

latestIgtvVideos.title: CHOKHI DHANI, JAIPUR
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Chokhi Dhani, translated from Rajasthani, literally means “Rajasthani Culture” and this resort village is a celebration of just that.💖
@chokhidhani is a well-known tourist attraction in Jaipur. The aim of the resort is to give tourists a full experience of Rajasthani culture. The entire resort’s theme is inspired by a village setting, with many cultural activities held here. The unique experience draws visitors from all over the world.🌍 

The @chokhidhani resort was started in 1989 and is sprawled across 10 acres of land, with unique architecture that reflects the grandeur of the Rajasthani tradition. The architecture is heavily influenced by the Indo-Saracenic style.💢

The resort houses a series of rebuilt village huts, complete with cow dung plasters and decorative wall paintings. The rooms at the resort are equipped with comfortable amenities and great facilities. You can spend a wonderful day here with your family and loved ones.👪 

Thank you @mayankraheja1604
for helping me to collect these beautiful moments. 

.
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: A visit to Gun Hill, Jawahar Aqarium, Mussorie Lake & Bhatta Falls
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
A)  Gun Hill : second highest peak of Mussorie. This is favourite place for viewing picturesque Himalayan range and Doon Valley. A popular view point of Mussoorie, located at 400 ft above The Mall and accessible by a cable car as well. A cable ride takes you to this place. There are eateries, local stuff shops and some activities for kids to do, including video games etc. Can see the hill station from a telescope. Nothing much to explore just a feel good place. The cable ride is indeed memorable.🚡
B) Jawahar Aquarium : Nice little aquarium is situated on mall road after some distance from Gun Hill Rope way point. The guide explains the species nicely. Good place if you like fishes. 🐠 
C) Mussorie Lake : Mussoorie lake is one of the popular attractions in Mussoorie. View and lake water is nice and clean. It's an artificial lake which was near out hotel. Nothing much but a quiet place. One has to walk down to get to it. Good place for some fun in evening. Small nice place to do boating. There are ducks to see, boating to do and paragliding too. Its just some kilometers before mussoorie. Good for an hour. 🚣 
D) Bhatta Falls : Bhatta Falls is a recently developed picnic spot near Mussoorie. Located at about 7 kms from main Mussoorie city, Bhatta Falls is still untouched by commercialization and has a natural stream of water flowing down the hills. After you reach here, there are plenty of things that you can do to recreate yourself in the lush greenery and the beauty of the place. 🌊
.
.
Special thanks to @mayankraheja1604
who helped me explore such beautiful places. 
.
